1
00:00:20,961 --> 00:00:23,930
I'm here now!

2
00:01:36,703 --> 00:01:39,729
Can we hope for the same gesture
of humanity from Pakistan?

3
00:01:40,307 --> 00:01:42,537
I can't speak to the Indian Army
General like this...

4
00:01:42,776 --> 00:01:44,744
let's simplify this...
- Sir, General Bakshi has arrived!

5
00:01:45,112 --> 00:01:47,410
Already?
- Should I ask him to go back?

6
00:02:04,698 --> 00:02:07,326
Cameras off! No cameras
before the show begins

7
00:02:08,402 --> 00:02:10,461
Are you in charge here?
- Yes sir!

8
00:02:10,704 --> 00:02:13,172
Not anymore!
I'm Brigadier Shekhar Sharma.

9
00:02:13,707 --> 00:02:15,572
The General's security
is my responsibility

10
00:02:15,943 --> 00:02:17,467
Any problems with that?
- Not at all sir!

11
00:02:17,711 --> 00:02:18,678
Good!

12
00:02:19,012 --> 00:02:21,503
Capt. Vikram, Major Abbas...
over there

13
00:02:22,716 --> 00:02:23,683
Major Karan

14
00:02:24,184 --> 00:02:25,913
Come with me

15
00:02:31,458 --> 00:02:33,585
Sir, security camera is in position.
- Good!

16
00:02:34,962 --> 00:02:37,430
All positions secured?
- Yes sir. All positions secured

17
00:02:37,631 --> 00:02:39,064
Good. Let the show begin

18
00:02:41,735 --> 00:02:43,703
Ladies and gentlemen,
welcome to 'People's Voice'

19
00:02:44,137 --> 00:02:48,540
I'm your host, Rajat Saxena
and today's issue is:

20
00:02:48,976 --> 00:02:55,040
Project Milaap (Unity), a historic
step or a historic mistake?

21
00:02:59,920 --> 00:03:02,889
The dawn of 15th of August,
our Independence Day...

22
00:03:03,357 --> 00:03:08,454
will see 50 Pakistani prisoners
in Indian custody released...

23
00:03:08,695 --> 00:03:10,458
at the Indian border

24
00:03:12,266 --> 00:03:16,498
Let's meet the man
behind Project Milaap

25
00:03:17,037 --> 00:03:19,904
Please welcome General
Amar Singh Bakshi...

26
00:03:20,207 --> 00:03:22,573
the Commander in Chief
of the Indian Army

27
00:03:31,351 --> 00:03:35,481
We'd first like to
congratulate you sir, because...

28
00:03:36,123 --> 00:03:40,025
the Parliament actually agreed
to Project Milaap this very morning!

29
00:03:43,964 --> 00:03:48,924
General Bakshi, do you really
believe that Project Milaap...

30
00:03:49,670 --> 00:03:51,638
will lead to friendship
between India and Pakistan?

31
00:03:52,172 --> 00:03:55,869
It's not so simple.
A chasm of fifty five years...

32
00:03:56,910 --> 00:03:59,538
cannot be bridged
by releasing fifty prisoners

33
00:04:00,013 --> 00:04:06,213
Then why Project Milaap?
- It's a step... to cover the miles

34
00:04:06,486 --> 00:04:09,455
So according to you
they are all innocent!

35
00:04:09,923 --> 00:04:13,882
None of them are terrorists
or ISI agents?

36
00:04:14,261 --> 00:04:17,560
If we had a shred of doubt that
they are dangerous to India...

37
00:04:18,131 --> 00:04:20,099
we would never have
taken this step

38
00:04:20,934 --> 00:04:24,335
Most of them
are poor villagers...

39
00:04:24,938 --> 00:04:27,304
who didn't even know
they had crossed the border

40
00:04:28,642 --> 00:04:31,270
After all the border is not
completely sealed

41
00:04:32,379 --> 00:04:34,347
They didn't even have weapons...

42
00:04:35,115 --> 00:04:39,518
yet they have been in our prisons
for years... some since 1971

43
00:04:40,253 --> 00:04:44,189
We feel it's time to
send them back home

44
00:04:47,494 --> 00:04:50,361
But not everyone agrees
with you General

45
00:04:51,665 --> 00:04:53,929
Some even want to stop you

46
00:04:55,235 --> 00:04:59,069
Everyone has the right to
free speech in a democracy!

47
00:05:00,240 --> 00:05:02,470
But some people
don't want to merely speak

48
00:05:04,177 --> 00:05:06,873
Sir, I'm talking about Raghavan

49
00:05:08,315 --> 00:05:11,284
The people would like to know
who Raghavan is...

50
00:05:12,519 --> 00:05:18,151
and is it true that
he has sworn to stop Project Milaap?

51
00:05:18,458 --> 00:05:23,896
Raghavan is a mask. He hides
his face because of his shame

52
00:05:25,198 --> 00:05:27,598
He's a coward - a terrorist...

53
00:05:28,435 --> 00:05:31,404
so used to violence
that he now fears peace

54
00:05:31,938 --> 00:05:33,906
Project Milaap
will be successful

55
00:05:34,941 --> 00:05:38,433
The prisoners will certainly be
released on the dawn of 15th August

56
00:06:02,235 --> 00:06:05,204
Damn! Back up!
We need back up immediately

57
00:06:18,118 --> 00:06:19,016
Come in

58
00:06:19,920 --> 00:06:21,888
Major Ram reporting, sir!
I'm outside the studio

59
00:06:22,189 --> 00:06:26,888
Maj. Ram, hold position for
two minutes! Back up is arriving

60
00:06:27,127 --> 00:06:29,220
It's too late, sir.
I'm going in

61
00:06:42,409 --> 00:06:47,403
Hello General. I'm Raghavan.
I'll ask you the remaining questions

62
00:06:51,952 --> 00:06:56,855
So General, I'm sure Pakistan is also
releasing our poor villagers, right?

63
00:06:57,290 --> 00:06:59,850
Exactly what
I was going to ask him!

64
00:07:02,596 --> 00:07:04,860
When elders speak,
learn to shut up!

65
00:07:10,537 --> 00:07:15,372
So General, what about
Pakistan's show of good will?

66
00:07:16,910 --> 00:07:19,140
We haven't heard anything
from Pakistan yet

67
00:07:20,180 --> 00:07:22,876
Then why are we being
so damn foolish?

68
00:07:23,250 --> 00:07:25,878
Because someone has to
take the first step

69
00:07:26,586 --> 00:07:30,147
If we all behave like you,
there will never be peace

70
00:07:30,457 --> 00:07:33,551
We've thought about this a lot

71
00:07:34,928 --> 00:07:38,125
And we are certain
that Pakistan will reciprocate

72
00:07:39,699 --> 00:07:42,566
Pakistan! Pakistan is going
to laugh at us...

73
00:07:43,603 --> 00:07:46,071
because they don't want peace.
- Why?

74
00:07:47,107 --> 00:07:49,575
Don't the Pakistanis
love their children?

75
00:07:50,443 --> 00:07:55,073
You do, General!
You love your daughter a lot

76
00:08:05,158 --> 00:08:06,352
Too bad!

77
00:08:07,894 --> 00:08:09,862
She will really miss you, General

78
00:08:10,297 --> 00:08:11,924
No one can save you now

79
00:10:58,431 --> 00:10:59,557
Ram!

80
00:11:31,064 --> 00:11:34,465
Easy now.
You'll be all right, Sharma

81
00:11:35,135 --> 00:11:36,932
Ambulance is on the way

82
00:11:37,971 --> 00:11:40,269
I want to speak to my son

83
00:11:45,478 --> 00:11:46,445
Ram...

84
00:11:52,719 --> 00:11:53,947
Father...

85
00:12:40,967 --> 00:12:42,264
Ram...
- Father...

86
00:12:44,737 --> 00:12:45,704
Please...

87
00:12:46,973 --> 00:12:49,601
Was I a good father?
- Yes father, but right now...

88
00:12:50,176 --> 00:12:54,078
No, tell me!

89
00:12:54,581 --> 00:12:57,209
You're the best father
in the whole world

90
00:12:57,917 --> 00:13:00,477
I'm guilty son!
- No, father

91
00:13:01,921 --> 00:13:03,889
Ram, listen please!

92
00:13:06,259 --> 00:13:09,023
There's something
I've always hidden from you

93
00:13:11,598 --> 00:13:12,895
You...

94
00:13:16,936 --> 00:13:24,399
You're not my only son

95
00:13:41,961 --> 00:13:44,395
I have a wife, Madhu

96
00:13:46,432 --> 00:13:48,593
And a son, Lakshman...

97
00:13:49,969 --> 00:13:53,530
your step... your brother!

98
00:13:55,074 --> 00:13:57,042
Who I haven't seen
for twenty years

99
00:14:11,724 --> 00:14:14,215
It's been twenty years
since she left me

100
00:14:15,929 --> 00:14:19,888
Twenty years I have lived
away from them

101
00:14:21,935 --> 00:14:25,894
It's time I pay for my deeds.
- Don't say this father

102
00:14:30,276 --> 00:14:34,906
I knew you'll forgive me Ram.
Your heart is big

103
00:14:36,583 --> 00:14:40,917
But until she forgives me
I will not find peace

104
00:14:46,426 --> 00:14:49,589
My family will remain broken...
scattered

105
00:14:51,764 --> 00:14:58,135
Promise me Ram, that you will
not immerse my ashes alone...

106
00:14:58,605 --> 00:15:02,097
that both my sons will
do my last rites

107
00:15:32,639 --> 00:15:34,504
Where is father's family?

108
00:15:34,974 --> 00:15:38,501
Son, they left
nineteen years back...

109
00:15:40,246 --> 00:15:44,910
Because I came here, right?

110
00:15:48,087 --> 00:15:52,183
Dear Shekhar, I know you consider
what happened between us...

111
00:15:53,026 --> 00:15:54,857
ten years back
a big mistake

112
00:15:56,329 --> 00:16:00,629
I stayed away from you as I knew
how much you loved your wife

113
00:16:02,035 --> 00:16:03,866
But today I'm helpless

114
00:16:04,904 --> 00:16:08,203
By the time you get this letter
I may not be alive

115
00:16:10,109 --> 00:16:12,873
I leave our son in your care

116
00:16:14,480 --> 00:16:18,211
Please look after him.
He is your son, too

117
00:16:20,920 --> 00:16:23,218
What's your name, son?
- Ram Sharma, sir!

118
00:16:30,930 --> 00:16:32,227
Madhu... please

119
00:16:33,066 --> 00:16:35,899
It was just a mistake

120
00:16:36,936 --> 00:16:38,563
It was just a mistake.
- Mistake?

121
00:16:39,038 --> 00:16:41,905
After marriage
it's called Infidelity, Shekhar

122
00:16:42,341 --> 00:16:45,902
I'm leaving. I can't live
with this lie anymore

123
00:16:46,345 --> 00:16:50,577
Lie? Are you calling
our marriage, our son a lie?

124
00:16:52,051 --> 00:16:54,383
And what about the one
who is sitting outside...

125
00:16:55,221 --> 00:16:57,189
your illegitimate son?

126
00:16:59,125 --> 00:17:00,854
He's a truth too

127
00:17:01,894 --> 00:17:04,454
And if he enters the house,
I am leaving

128
00:17:05,331 --> 00:17:08,232
Where will he go?
It's not his fault

129
00:17:08,901 --> 00:17:11,529
You're right Shekhar.
It's not his fault

130
00:17:12,238 --> 00:17:14,536
It's my fault
for having trusted you

131
00:17:46,105 --> 00:17:47,902
For my sake...

132
00:17:48,541 --> 00:17:50,907
because of me, father
stayed away from his family

133
00:17:55,548 --> 00:17:58,847
I will bring them home

134
00:17:59,886 --> 00:18:04,448
They won't come home, son,
not till you're here

135
00:18:10,496 --> 00:18:13,397
You can't go anywhere
at this stage, Ram

136
00:18:13,966 --> 00:18:16,867
I need you till 15th August.
- I know, sir

137
00:18:17,904 --> 00:18:20,532
But I made a promise
to my father

138
00:18:21,340 --> 00:18:25,470
Then go ahead.
Project Milaap was his dream too

139
00:18:27,613 --> 00:18:31,049
Ram, this is the photograph
Raghavan gave me

140
00:18:32,418 --> 00:18:35,387
It's my daughter Sanjana,
in her college in Darjeeling

141
00:18:36,355 --> 00:18:38,323
This picture was taken
from her college

142
00:18:38,925 --> 00:18:43,328
A gun can reach where a camera can.
And it's my worst fear

143
00:18:43,930 --> 00:18:46,421
Sir, why don't you call her back?
- Because she won't agree

144
00:18:47,066 --> 00:18:50,229
Even if her life's in danger?
- You don't know my daughter, Ram

145
00:18:51,637 --> 00:18:53,901
I haven't seen her
for two years

146
00:18:56,042 --> 00:18:57,907
She hates me

147
00:19:00,546 --> 00:19:05,074
Of course, it's my fault entirely.
I never let her come close to me

148
00:19:06,552 --> 00:19:11,922
I wanted a son. A son,
who would join the army like me

149
00:19:13,726 --> 00:19:17,093
That's why I never loved her...

150
00:19:18,965 --> 00:19:20,933
like I would've loved my son

151
00:19:24,136 --> 00:19:26,604
Today I can give anything
to catch her glimpse...

152
00:19:27,974 --> 00:19:29,339
but she won't let me

153
00:19:30,643 --> 00:19:33,942
Sir, can we not send a 24 hour
Protection Team for her surveillance?

154
00:19:34,413 --> 00:19:36,938
Sanjana will never let anyone
in a uniform come close to her

155
00:19:37,683 --> 00:19:42,347
If anyone does, she will run away
...she's done it before

156
00:19:44,323 --> 00:19:46,951
So what do you recommend sir?
- I want you...

157
00:19:47,360 --> 00:19:51,558
to go to Darjeeling,
under cover to protect Sanjana

158
00:19:52,765 --> 00:19:54,494
I don't trust anyone else

159
00:19:54,934 --> 00:20:00,236
I'm sorry, sir. It's impossible for me
to go to Darjeeling right now

160
00:20:01,507 --> 00:20:03,907
I thought you may be interested
in this mission...

161
00:20:04,944 --> 00:20:09,540
as there's another student,
Lakshman Sharma, studying there

162
00:20:13,953 --> 00:20:17,912
Your father and I've been friends
for 25 years. I know everything

163
00:20:18,958 --> 00:20:20,926
Call it fate or co-incidence...

164
00:20:21,494 --> 00:20:25,328
but his wife Madhu and
his son Lakshman live in Darjeeling

165
00:20:26,465 --> 00:20:28,592
You are now officially on leave
till 15th August

166
00:20:29,435 --> 00:20:31,403
I've already spoken
to the Principal of St. Paul's

167
00:20:32,038 --> 00:20:33,938
You are joining the college
from Monday

168
00:20:35,675 --> 00:20:37,939
And what subject
will I teach there?

169
00:20:38,311 --> 00:20:41,280
You are not going there as a teacher
...you will be a student

170
00:20:44,050 --> 00:20:46,280
I'll look really strange
as a student, sir

171
00:20:46,652 --> 00:20:48,950
I think I'm better off as a teacher.
- You can't stay with Sanjana...

172
00:20:49,155 --> 00:20:52,522
all the time as a teacher.
- But I just don't look like a student

173
00:20:52,992 --> 00:20:55,483
Besides, it's been ages since I
attended the national Defence College

174
00:20:55,962 --> 00:21:00,899
Don't worry. Even the principal
will say that you are there...

175
00:21:01,267 --> 00:21:03,235
to complete your graduation
which was left incomplete

176
00:21:03,469 --> 00:21:06,563
But sir, the current generation...?
I've never even seen a civil college

177
00:21:07,273 --> 00:21:10,401
I'll be caught in a day!
- Ram, no matter what...

178
00:21:11,277 --> 00:21:13,245
Project Milaap cannot stop!

179
00:21:13,946 --> 00:21:16,244
Those prisoners have to be released
on 15th August

180
00:21:17,950 --> 00:21:19,542
But Sanjana's safety...?

181
00:21:19,952 --> 00:21:21,920
No harm will come to Sanjana

182
00:21:22,955 --> 00:21:25,253
I promise you, sir.
- Thank you, Major

183
00:22:08,334 --> 00:22:11,895
"Like the winds sigh..."

184
00:22:12,338 --> 00:22:15,899
"and the birds fly..."

185
00:22:16,342 --> 00:22:19,903
"like the bumble bee's affair..."

186
00:22:20,346 --> 00:22:23,907
"I roam without a care"

187
00:22:32,291 --> 00:22:35,920
"I'm the queen of hearts!
What sadness is, I know not"

188
00:22:36,362 --> 00:22:39,263
"With no fear,
I do and I defy"

189
00:22:39,965 --> 00:22:47,497
"Like the winds sigh,
and the birds fly..."

190
00:23:15,267 --> 00:23:19,294
"They can halt, they can try,
they can stop and ask me why..."

191
00:23:19,705 --> 00:23:22,435
"but do I listen,
oh no, not l"

192
00:23:23,275 --> 00:23:26,904
"I'm stubborn,
I'm crazy..."

193
00:23:27,413 --> 00:23:30,246
"They say my mind is hazy..."

194
00:23:30,950 --> 00:23:38,254
"but no one knows
where my dreams lie"

195
00:23:38,757 --> 00:23:45,925
"Like the winds sigh,
and the birds fly..."

196
00:23:46,398 --> 00:23:53,930
"Like the bumble bee's affair,
I roam without a care"

197
00:24:02,314 --> 00:24:05,875
"I'm the queen of hearts,
What sadness is, I know not"

198
00:24:06,285 --> 00:24:09,311
"With no fear,
I do and I defy"

199
00:24:26,205 --> 00:24:31,233
It's odd, I've never seen my brother,
I've no clue what he looks like

200
00:24:31,744 --> 00:24:34,907
But I'm certain
his eyes will be like mine

201
00:24:41,654 --> 00:24:43,918
Actually I think he'd be
exactly like me...

202
00:24:44,323 --> 00:24:46,917
calm, shy, decent, disciplined

203
00:24:55,935 --> 00:24:58,199
And my heart says I will
recognize him instantly...

204
00:24:59,438 --> 00:25:01,065
my little Lakshman

205
00:25:12,985 --> 00:25:16,580
"Let the nymphets
come to lure me"

206
00:25:17,256 --> 00:25:19,884
"And know that I'm no worker bee"

207
00:25:20,926 --> 00:25:24,453
"For when I look into their eyes,
I'll steal their hearts, their minds"

208
00:25:24,997 --> 00:25:27,989
"No matter how gorgeous..."

209
00:25:28,934 --> 00:25:35,567
"they'll be mine
without a fuss"

210
00:25:36,141 --> 00:25:39,599
"Like the winds sigh..."

211
00:25:40,112 --> 00:25:43,377
"and the birds fly..."

212
00:25:43,949 --> 00:25:47,407
"Like the bumble bee's affair..."

213
00:25:47,953 --> 00:25:51,445
"I roam without a care"

214
00:26:00,332 --> 00:26:03,392
"I may be mad, a little strange,
and wilder than most..."

215
00:26:03,936 --> 00:26:06,871
"but the most lovable,
am everybody's toast"

216
00:26:07,573 --> 00:26:10,872
"Like the winds sigh..."

217
00:26:11,310 --> 00:26:14,871
"and the birds fly..."

218
00:26:15,247 --> 00:26:18,876
"Like the bumble bee's affair..."

219
00:26:19,318 --> 00:26:22,879
"I roam without a care"

220
00:26:51,083 --> 00:26:58,182
Friends, it's a truly blessed day
as today we have amongst us...

221
00:26:58,490 --> 00:27:00,458
the famous student
of St. Paul's, Lucky!

222
00:27:04,897 --> 00:27:08,196
When I came to this college
four years back, Lucky was my senior

223
00:27:08,400 --> 00:27:12,427
When we first got here,
Lucky ragged us a lot, didn't he?

224
00:27:13,072 --> 00:27:17,441
In the canteen, he stripped me and
made me sing 'My heart will go on... '

225
00:27:19,945 --> 00:27:21,879
He's as smooth as so charming,
smooth and perky

226
00:27:22,014 --> 00:27:23,982
We wanna fail school
just like Lucky!

227
00:27:24,183 --> 00:27:25,878
I love Lucky!

228
00:27:26,151 --> 00:27:30,315
Despite having failed his class
thrice, Lucky is still with us

229
00:27:30,589 --> 00:27:33,558
And God willing,
Lucky may fail again...

230
00:27:33,926 --> 00:27:36,486
and bless our juniors
with his presence too

231
00:27:36,929 --> 00:27:38,897
And now, the moment
we've been waiting for...

232
00:27:43,936 --> 00:27:45,563
Yes, it wasn't easy!

233
00:27:46,004 --> 00:27:48,495
To fail consecutively thrice,
is not an ordinary feat!

234
00:27:51,009 --> 00:27:56,003
But friends, with hard work,
perseverance and dedication...

235
00:27:56,482 --> 00:27:58,848
you can all get here

236
00:28:00,886 --> 00:28:05,346
And if I have your blessings,
I will continue to be with you...

237
00:28:05,891 --> 00:28:10,089
right here, in this college,
for eons to come

238
00:28:10,896 --> 00:28:12,864
That's a promise

239
00:28:22,074 --> 00:28:24,042
Don't you feel any shame?
- Shame, Sanju?

240
00:28:24,443 --> 00:28:28,971
Just look at these faces,
full of love, respect

241
00:28:29,982 --> 00:28:31,950
And I won't need to study
this year as well

