453
00:40:39,935 --> 00:40:41,562
Who is dropping you home by the way?

454
00:40:41,770 --> 00:40:43,567
I'm a big girl I'll drive myself
home in my car.

455
00:40:43,772 --> 00:40:46,240
True. But a lady should be
escorted to her car

456
00:40:46,675 --> 00:40:49,906
Please don't take the trouble
- Oh no. I don't mean me

457
00:40:50,212 --> 00:40:52,578
I mean your favorite student. Ram

458
00:40:52,948 --> 00:40:54,575
Sir.
- Come here

459
00:40:55,617 --> 00:40:57,244
Won't you escort
Ms Chandni to her car?

460
00:40:57,619 --> 00:40:59,587
Really, there's no need for you to...
- No, no.

461
00:40:59,955 --> 00:41:01,582
I...
- Actually

462
00:41:02,024 --> 00:41:03,924
Please go with her
- Yes, sir

463
00:41:09,565 --> 00:41:12,864
Target approaching door. Handle it.
- Yes, sir

464
00:41:14,903 --> 00:41:18,600
I'm sorry you were
forced to escort me, Ram

465
00:41:18,807 --> 00:41:21,605
I love it, ma'am.
I mean, it's my duty

466
00:41:23,912 --> 00:41:27,075
You really dance superbly.
Where did you learn?

467
00:41:27,649 --> 00:41:30,277
Actually, whenever I see you,
I feel like a fish out of water...

468
00:41:30,719 --> 00:41:33,279
A nut without a cracker...
- Oh no. Not again

469
00:41:33,655 --> 00:41:36,055
Actually Sanju, Lucky,
Vivek and Mini forced me...

470
00:41:36,425 --> 00:41:38,154
Your sari is lovely

471
00:41:44,666 --> 00:41:49,569
Ram, if you drive
as well as you dance...?

472
00:41:51,607 --> 00:41:53,575
Won't you drop me home?

473
00:42:52,334 --> 00:42:53,232
Ram!

474
00:42:56,705 --> 00:42:58,172
C'mon!
- Ram!

475
00:42:58,840 --> 00:43:00,137
Get out!

476
00:43:01,910 --> 00:43:04,242
Stop! Put the gun down
or I'll blow her brains out

477
00:43:04,780 --> 00:43:06,577
Ram, listen to him!

478
00:43:07,649 --> 00:43:09,583
Down!
- Down...

479
00:43:27,436 --> 00:43:29,597
Sorry about the sari, ma'am

480
00:43:31,440 --> 00:43:32,407
It's no problem

481
00:43:35,677 --> 00:43:37,872
Thanks for the lift, sir.
But you needn't have bothered

482
00:43:38,580 --> 00:43:40,548
We would have managed.
- Don't be silly

483
00:43:41,016 --> 00:43:42,984
How would you go back
home alone, and at this hour?

484
00:43:43,585 --> 00:43:47,214
Son, you never know
who you might meet on the way

485
00:43:48,590 --> 00:43:50,558
Sir, I get off here

486
00:43:55,030 --> 00:43:56,827
Thank you, sir.
- Sure

487
00:43:58,934 --> 00:44:01,232
Won't you get out and
thank your friend Sanju?

488
00:44:01,770 --> 00:44:03,567
Go ahead. It's okay

489
00:44:05,607 --> 00:44:07,768
Good night, Lucky!

490
00:44:16,318 --> 00:44:17,285
Hold it!

491
00:44:19,621 --> 00:44:22,181
What the hell is happening?
Ram, a gun...?

492
00:44:22,624 --> 00:44:24,922
Sir, please just keep driving.
Move it!

493
00:44:26,294 --> 00:44:28,262
What's going on, Ram?
- Towards the hostel! I'll explain

494
00:44:28,697 --> 00:44:29,925
Pull over, sir

495
00:44:40,042 --> 00:44:43,102
Sanjana, your dad is here.
Go and talk to him

496
00:44:55,590 --> 00:44:58,991
I'm sorry, Papa.
- No, my dear. I'm sorry

497
00:45:03,932 --> 00:45:06,560
Thanks for dropping us here, sir.
- It was my duty

498
00:45:09,738 --> 00:45:11,569
So you're in the army?

499
00:45:14,609 --> 00:45:15,974
Major Ram, sir

500
00:45:17,612 --> 00:45:19,978
Major, impressive

501
00:45:21,149 --> 00:45:25,745
Glad to know that country's security
is in such able hands

502
00:45:27,689 --> 00:45:30,180
Any doubts, sir?
- Absolutely not

503
00:45:31,026 --> 00:45:32,152
Good night.
- Good night

504
00:45:40,569 --> 00:45:42,196
Papa... Ram...?

505
00:45:43,238 --> 00:45:46,105
I had sent Ram,
for your protection

506
00:46:09,297 --> 00:46:10,559
So...

507
00:46:15,203 --> 00:46:17,171
you're in the army, right?

508
00:46:17,606 --> 00:46:19,233
No... yes ma'am

509
00:46:21,943 --> 00:46:24,571
You're here to protect Sanjana?

510
00:46:26,615 --> 00:46:29,140
Yes... yes ma'am

511
00:46:32,654 --> 00:46:36,988
So you never really were my student?

512
00:46:38,260 --> 00:46:42,219
Yes ma'am... I mean, no ma'am

513
00:46:50,972 --> 00:46:52,701
Happy Teacher's Day

514
00:46:57,712 --> 00:46:59,543
Thank you, sir... ma'am

515
00:47:00,916 --> 00:47:02,884
Ram! Come in, come in, Ram!

516
00:47:03,652 --> 00:47:07,088
Sir, we should congratulate
Major Ram on his successful mission

517
00:47:07,589 --> 00:47:09,557
Has he succeeded?
Very good

518
00:47:09,925 --> 00:47:11,722
So you finally
found Lakshman Prasad Sharma

519
00:47:15,130 --> 00:47:18,566
No sir. Sanjana Bakshi.
General Bakshi's daughter

520
00:47:18,800 --> 00:47:20,700
General Bakshi? Does he want
admission to the college as well?

521
00:47:20,869 --> 00:47:22,734
No, General Bakshi is not joining

522
00:47:26,308 --> 00:47:28,572
Sir, I have a request.
- Feel free to speak, Maximus

523
00:47:30,178 --> 00:47:32,146
I'd like to stay here a bit longer

524
00:47:32,948 --> 00:47:35,576
Then you must have lunch and go
- No, I mean...

525
00:47:35,951 --> 00:47:37,680
I'd like to stay in college
for a few more days

526
00:47:37,886 --> 00:47:40,116
Then stay till graduation.
- Okay

527
00:47:40,889 --> 00:47:44,325
But please don't
mention this to anyone

528
00:47:44,893 --> 00:47:46,087
Top secret?

529
00:47:48,630 --> 00:47:52,532
Sir!
- Of course. Anything for the army

530
00:47:54,336 --> 00:47:56,531
Thank you, sir! Thank you!

531
00:48:00,675 --> 00:48:02,802
Lakshman Sharma. Lucky, right?

532
00:48:03,044 --> 00:48:06,207
His distant relative. Had come
all the way here to find him

533
00:48:08,049 --> 00:48:09,016
Lucky me

534
00:48:10,051 --> 00:48:11,951
You have 6 hours

535
00:48:12,387 --> 00:48:15,879
Find out the relationship between
Major Ram And Lakshman Prasad

536
00:48:16,725 --> 00:48:19,057
So, when do you plan to
tell your mother?

537
00:48:19,594 --> 00:48:21,892
Even Sanjana has agreed
to protection

538
00:48:22,330 --> 00:48:25,561
You must reveal your identity...
- I know, Chandni

539
00:48:27,102 --> 00:48:28,660
But I'm apprehensive

540
00:48:33,275 --> 00:48:35,243
So Lucky Sharma is
Shekhar Sharma's son

541
00:48:35,877 --> 00:48:38,846
Ram's step-brother.
Sweet

542
00:48:39,314 --> 00:48:42,112
Look Ram, if they find out
from elsewhere...

543
00:48:42,550 --> 00:48:44,848
then they are bound to feel that
you deliberately deceived them

544
00:48:46,888 --> 00:48:51,086
And once they know who you are
I'm sure they'll love you even more

545
00:48:51,927 --> 00:48:56,523
I see. So once you found out,
you loved me even more, eh?

546
00:48:57,232 --> 00:48:58,699
Any doubts?

547
00:48:59,634 --> 00:49:02,068
Gentlemen, get ready for action!

548
00:49:03,571 --> 00:49:06,131
Tomorrow Major Ram will leave
for a long exile

549
00:49:12,013 --> 00:49:15,073
Keep watching dad,
this time mom will accept me

550
00:49:16,818 --> 00:49:18,786
Lakshman will, too

551
00:49:40,208 --> 00:49:41,573
Hello Ma

552
00:49:41,977 --> 00:49:42,944
Lucky...

553
00:49:45,613 --> 00:49:46,580
Mother...

554
00:49:47,949 --> 00:49:50,577
I want to say some thing...

555
00:49:51,619 --> 00:49:54,588
to both of you actually

556
00:50:01,696 --> 00:50:04,187
Ram, you're Shekhar Sharma's son?

557
00:50:11,639 --> 00:50:14,267
And you never even mentioned it to me?
The army officers told me

558
00:50:15,043 --> 00:50:17,603
He's quite a wretch,
but a very dear friend

559
00:50:17,979 --> 00:50:20,777
We were in the same college.
Can you give me his address?

560
00:50:21,049 --> 00:50:22,778
Or a contact number?

561
00:50:28,390 --> 00:50:30,290
Is everything okay, son?

562
00:50:37,932 --> 00:50:40,560
Looks like I've come
at the wrong time

563
00:50:41,936 --> 00:50:42,903
Goodbye

564
00:50:52,614 --> 00:50:56,175
Mother I... I was just going
to tell you this...

565
00:50:56,618 --> 00:50:58,586
Just don't say anything!
Not a word! Shut up

566
00:50:58,953 --> 00:51:00,921
Mother, I hope you understand
why I behaved like this

567
00:51:01,189 --> 00:51:04,920
One more word Ram and...
- No Lakshman. Let him speak

568
00:51:06,628 --> 00:51:08,596
I do want to know
why he behaved like this

569
00:51:09,697 --> 00:51:12,666
Tell me, why did you sneak
into our lives?

570
00:51:16,704 --> 00:51:21,403
Did you think we'd accept you, and
forget everything?

571
00:51:23,878 --> 00:51:27,177
Will I forget the twenty years
I spent like a widow?

572
00:51:28,983 --> 00:51:31,349
Twenty years,
which will never return

573
00:51:34,089 --> 00:51:37,183
Did you think that if you
escort me to the temple once...

574
00:51:37,659 --> 00:51:40,287
and touch my feet,
everything will be set right?

575
00:51:41,396 --> 00:51:42,693
No, Ma

576
00:51:43,598 --> 00:51:47,762
Wounds twenty years deep do not
get filled in twenty days, Ram

577
00:51:49,737 --> 00:51:53,571
Go, tell your father that
we don't need him anymore...

578
00:51:54,609 --> 00:51:56,577
we're used to living without him

579
00:51:57,045 --> 00:52:00,014
And this is his penance too,
to live without us...

580
00:52:00,615 --> 00:52:02,276
and die without seeing our faces

581
00:52:05,186 --> 00:52:07,916
Pack up and leave

582
00:52:11,326 --> 00:52:13,590
There's no place
in my home for you even today

583
00:52:45,593 --> 00:52:47,220
Just a minute, Ram

584
00:52:50,665 --> 00:52:52,257
What were you hoping to achieve?

585
00:52:54,936 --> 00:52:58,167
Why did you do all this? Why?

586
00:53:00,842 --> 00:53:03,242
I had come here to fulfill
my father's last wish

587
00:53:11,286 --> 00:53:18,124
You were right. His penance was
to live without seeing the two of you

588
00:53:20,628 --> 00:53:22,596
And... he died without seeing
the two of you

589
00:53:35,643 --> 00:53:37,611
He loved you a lot

590
00:53:39,581 --> 00:53:42,209
Lucky, he gave me his ashes

591
00:53:46,154 --> 00:53:50,682
I just wanted to untie the family.
That's all

592
00:53:53,061 --> 00:53:55,552
Even though I knew
I would never be accepted

593
00:53:58,600 --> 00:54:00,227
I'm sorry

594
00:55:15,777 --> 00:55:18,075
"Bonds that break..."

595
00:55:19,047 --> 00:55:21,743
"loved ones ache"

596
00:55:23,618 --> 00:55:28,146
"I hope the miles finds a bridge"

597
00:55:29,123 --> 00:55:31,591
"Why does this happen?"

598
00:55:32,393 --> 00:55:35,089
"Why does the heart bleed?"

599
00:55:36,631 --> 00:55:41,534
"Why am I tongue-tied?"

600
00:55:50,278 --> 00:55:54,977
"I leave my dearest here and how..."

601
00:55:55,583 --> 00:56:02,546
I walk alone, I'm here now"

602
00:56:03,658 --> 00:56:08,561
"It's me who found love,
yet lost it"

603
00:56:10,098 --> 00:56:15,559
"Here I am...
restless and unsettled"

604
00:56:37,358 --> 00:56:38,256
Sir

605
00:56:38,626 --> 00:56:40,594
Yes, sir.
What?

606
00:56:43,765 --> 00:56:47,201
Sanju, look up.
Say hello to your dad

607
00:56:47,668 --> 00:56:50,535
So what now, General Bakshi?
Sanjana's with me now

608
00:56:51,172 --> 00:56:53,106
Are you still ready
to sacrifice her...

609
00:56:53,674 --> 00:56:54,641
him...

610
00:56:56,010 --> 00:56:56,977
him...

611
00:56:58,913 --> 00:57:00,005
and all the others?

612
00:57:00,214 --> 00:57:03,240
I don't think so, Gen. Bakshi.
Project Milaap (Unity) is finished!

613
00:57:03,918 --> 00:57:05,215
I have a few more demands

614
00:57:05,586 --> 00:57:08,714
My soldier Khan's release,
a helicopter...

615
00:57:09,257 --> 00:57:11,691
and my favorite student Major Ram

616
00:57:17,965 --> 00:57:20,263
His education is still incomplete

617
00:57:37,618 --> 00:57:39,848
Check the corridors again
- Sir

618
00:57:47,028 --> 00:57:48,518
Breaking news this evening!

619
00:57:48,696 --> 00:57:51,529
The Pakistan General has announced
that on 15th August...

620
00:57:51,833 --> 00:57:56,861
they will reciprocate by returning
Indian POW's to India as well

621
00:57:57,271 --> 00:57:59,136
If one extends such a warm hand
of friendship...

622
00:57:59,340 --> 00:58:01,240
even Pakistan isn't so cold as to
not reciprocate

623
00:58:01,642 --> 00:58:06,341
It's a pity that
we didn't take the first step

624
00:58:07,081 --> 00:58:09,879
We've won. Now he'll have
to release those kids

625
00:58:10,184 --> 00:58:13,153
Nothing has changed, General.
Pakistan can do what they want

626
00:58:14,288 --> 00:58:16,256
You will not release the enemy

627
00:58:17,792 --> 00:58:21,558
And by the way, I hope Khan
is near the helicopter...

628
00:58:22,597 --> 00:58:24,724
and Ram has been tied up

629
00:58:25,600 --> 00:58:29,161
Because Sanjana and her friends
have very little time left

630
00:58:29,837 --> 00:58:32,567
But sir, didn't we say that
if Pakistan releases our prisoners...

631
00:58:32,773 --> 00:58:37,574
An old habit of theirs. One hand
tries to put balm on the wound...

632
00:58:38,112 --> 00:58:40,672
and the other hand hides a dagger
for the attack

633
00:58:41,549 --> 00:58:43,517
Now you guys, get back
to your stations.

634
00:58:43,985 --> 00:58:46,180
We're expecting guests

635
00:58:57,011 --> 00:59:00,572
Call the Prime minister's office,
and tell him that...

636
00:59:01,282 --> 00:59:03,716
Project Milaap has been
indefinitely postponed

637
00:59:05,453 --> 00:59:07,648
Inform the
Pakistani Ambassador as well

638
00:59:09,390 --> 00:59:10,584
No, sir

639
00:59:12,360 --> 00:59:14,260
Sir, please don't do this.
- No Ram

640
00:59:14,963 --> 00:59:18,763
There's a mother out there
who waits for her son

641
00:59:19,667 --> 00:59:21,965
Tomorrow there will be
several mothers sitting outside

642
00:59:25,740 --> 00:59:28,265
What will I possibly tell them?
That for fifty Pakistani prisoners...

643
00:59:28,576 --> 00:59:30,271
I had to sacrifice their children?

644
00:59:31,479 --> 00:59:34,607
Not fifty Pakistanis, sir.
It was you who used to say that...

645
00:59:35,083 --> 00:59:40,783
it's not about ten Indians or
Pakistanis but thousands of soldiers

646
00:59:41,723 --> 00:59:45,284
It's about the common people
in these countries. It's about us

647
00:59:46,327 --> 00:59:49,296
It's a question of an enmity which
neither of us chose voluntarily

648
00:59:49,531 --> 00:59:51,692
I know, Ram.
I understand this very well

649
00:59:53,601 --> 00:59:57,628
But maybe we need to wait
for that friendship a bit longer

650
00:59:58,072 --> 01:00:00,302
Sorry sir, but how long?

651
01:00:01,342 --> 01:00:03,970
Today, after eons, Pakistan has
extended a friendly hand towards us

652
01:00:05,413 --> 01:00:08,644
If we retract now, it would mean
another fifty years of enmity

653
01:00:10,018 --> 01:00:11,986
And this time sir,
we would have chosen it

654
01:00:12,420 --> 01:00:15,878
What happens to those children, Ram?
- Don't worry about the kids, sir

655
01:00:16,524 --> 01:00:20,927
I promise you. Tomorrow, before dawn,
all the kids will be free

656
01:00:21,796 --> 01:00:24,924
Please cancel your order, sir.
Prepare for Project Milaap

657
01:00:31,573 --> 01:00:34,337
Didn't you ask if Pakistan was ready
to release our prisoners too, Khan?

658
01:00:36,044 --> 01:00:38,808
You believed that Pakistan
would laugh at us...

659
01:00:40,315 --> 01:00:44,877
but Pakistan is reciprocating.
Like us, Pakistan also wants peace

660
01:00:46,554 --> 01:00:49,387
Yes, Pakistan is
releasing our prisoners

661
01:00:52,327 --> 01:00:56,627
Now what can Raghavan achieve
by killing those innocent children?

662
01:00:57,065 --> 01:00:59,033
Whatever he's doing,
it's for the country, Major Ram

663
01:00:59,400 --> 01:01:02,961
No, Khan. Major Raghavan Datta,
ex-army, court-martialled...

664
01:01:03,338 --> 01:01:05,829
is doing nothing for the country.
Nothing

665
01:01:07,342 --> 01:01:10,311
Did you know that he had son
who was killed in Kashmir...

666
01:01:10,612 --> 01:01:12,307
by terrorists such as you

667
01:01:12,780 --> 01:01:14,748
But Raghavan believes that
Pakistanis killed him

668
01:01:15,450 --> 01:01:17,008
Raghavan is doing nothing
for this country

669
01:01:17,352 --> 01:01:19,320
He is just carrying out
a misplaced vendetta

670
01:01:19,520 --> 01:01:22,318
It's just revenge, Khan.
- Impossible, Major Ram. You're lying

671
01:01:23,024 --> 01:01:25,322
Raghavan had said...
- Raghavan lied to you, Khan

672
01:01:25,827 --> 01:01:28,990
Didn't you say your war
is for the country?

673
01:01:30,698 --> 01:01:32,666
Well, tomorrow the gun will be
in your hand

674
01:01:34,369 --> 01:01:39,432
Choose. Will you fight
for you country or for Raghavan?

675
01:02:05,033 --> 01:02:07,763
You lost your home, your husband
because of me once

676
01:02:09,671 --> 01:02:11,639
I won't let you lose your son

677
01:02:14,342 --> 01:02:16,310
I assure you,
Lakshman will not be harmed

678
01:02:18,446 --> 01:02:20,311
I'm here now

679
01:02:28,156 --> 01:02:29,316
Ram...

680
01:02:33,761 --> 01:02:37,322
I want both my sons back

681
01:03:54,642 --> 01:03:55,609
Khan...

682
01:03:57,311 --> 01:03:59,279
Are you okay?
- I'm fine, sir

683
01:04:04,318 --> 01:04:06,843
Major, I thought you are
the very best

684
01:04:07,488 --> 01:04:10,719
I was right in front of you
and you couldn't even recognize me

685
01:04:11,492 --> 01:04:12,982
Let the children go, Raghavan

686
01:04:14,328 --> 01:04:18,287
You've got what you wanted and
Pakistan is also cooperating with us

687
01:04:19,333 --> 01:04:21,301
Yeah, yeah. I heard

688
01:04:22,770 --> 01:04:25,637
It is this naivety
that will sink us eventually

689
01:04:26,073 --> 01:04:28,974
No Raghavan. People like you
will sink us

690
01:04:29,677 --> 01:04:33,010
You only know to hate, shed blood

691
01:04:34,015 --> 01:04:36,813
You are so used to violence that
you can't bear the idea of peace

692
01:04:37,518 --> 01:04:40,248
But there will be peace,
there will be understanding

693
01:04:41,289 --> 01:04:43,917
And there will be friendship
- No friendship with Pakistan, Ram!

694
01:04:45,359 --> 01:04:49,853
Only war.
And one result. Pakistan's defeat

695
01:04:50,965 --> 01:04:52,933
Only then can the blood
on their hands...

696
01:04:54,302 --> 01:04:59,706
wipe away all the blood shed,
our soldiers, my son...

697
01:05:00,308 --> 01:05:03,277
who had nothing to do with the war.
Why did the Pakistanis kill him?

698
01:05:06,314 --> 01:05:09,875
His body lay atop a hill
in Kashmir for two days...

699
01:05:12,086 --> 01:05:14,611
on ice.
No one ever knew

700
01:05:16,657 --> 01:05:19,956
Ram, there will be no friendship
with Pakistan. I won't let it happen!

701
01:05:20,628 --> 01:05:22,823
You should think real hard
before you hate Raghavan...

702
01:05:23,397 --> 01:05:25,888
because one day you will become
exactly that what you detest the most

703
01:05:26,334 --> 01:05:27,301
Shut up, Ram

704
01:05:27,568 --> 01:05:29,968
Now you are going to kill
these innocent kids...

705
01:05:30,338 --> 01:05:32,704
and become what you once
hated the most. A filthy murderer!

706
01:05:33,341 --> 01:05:34,308
Silence!

707
01:05:36,143 --> 01:05:38,839
He has the blood of innocent people,
kids, on his hands

708
01:05:39,280 --> 01:05:40,975
I say shut up, Ram.
- Project Milaap won't stop.

709
01:05:42,283 --> 01:05:44,410
Project Milaap won't stop.
You've lost, Raghavan

710
01:05:44,552 --> 01:05:45,484
Silence!

711
01:05:46,754 --> 01:05:48,949
Go on, kill these kids
and avenge your son

712
01:05:50,892 --> 01:05:53,588
It won't stop Project Milaap.
You have lost, Raghavan

713
01:05:55,563 --> 01:05:56,530
Khan!

714
01:05:59,033 --> 01:06:01,263
No Khan. No, don't Khan

715
01:06:03,971 --> 01:06:05,768
Khan, don't

716
01:06:06,307 --> 01:06:08,275
Khan don't shoot. Damn it!

717
01:06:10,778 --> 01:06:12,939
Not now, Khan.
Put your gun down

718
01:07:14,542 --> 01:07:17,534
My war is still for my country.
- Khan...

719
01:07:17,912 --> 01:07:19,880
Fulfill the promise you made
to your mother

720
01:07:21,082 --> 01:07:22,947
We may not meet again.

721
01:07:25,419 --> 01:07:27,284
I wish you peace, Major

722
01:07:31,325 --> 01:07:32,952
You too, Khan

723
01:07:38,632 --> 01:07:41,829
Until Project Milaap
is cancelled we will stay here

724
01:07:42,269 --> 01:07:43,930
And what if it doesn't stop...?

725
01:07:46,273 --> 01:07:48,241
We'll have to kill the kids, Khan

726
01:07:49,010 --> 01:07:50,238
Shoot them

727
